newsitem.title: UK: NWE gasoline slightly firmer, sellers sidelined.
newsitem.headline: NWE gasoline slightly firmer, sellers sidelined.

text.p: NWE gasoline was slightly stronger on Friday in a deserted end-of-the-week market, traders said.
A Eurograde barge traded at $198.50 a tonne fob ARA for delivery up to May 10.
May swaps were talked around the $196/$197, and June paper was assessed some $3.50 lower.
Traders said sellers appeared reluctant to come into the market on the expectation that gasoline demand and prices were set to increase as May approached.
